The paper deals with the Physical Layer Security (PLS) problem in a multiuser transmission system, which involves resource allocation and power optimization. This makes it likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with security and eavesdropping, which makes it relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of OFDMA and relay nodes also makes it relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the optimization problem and use of Lagrangian dual decomposition suggest that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
